Calculate the change in direction during the response
=====================================================
Angle_time.m

Function:
Calculate the change in head to tail vector with respect to the average vector of first 60 frames

Output:
angle_*.mat

Structure of output:
angle_all: Change in direction (time x worm index). Range = +180 to -180 degrees. Clockwise = -ve. Output = NaN if vector length = 0.

Dependency:
Angle_change.m

======================================================
Angle_change.m

Function:
calculate the change in direction of vector2 wiht respect to vector 1 on a 2D plane

Input:
Angle_change(initvec,finalvec)
initvec : (x,y)
finalvec : (x,y)
The size of initvec and finalvec must be (1*2)

Output:
change in direction in degrees. Range = +180 to -180 degrees. Clockwise = -ve. Output = NaN if vector length = 0.
======================================================
